01:20:25,902 --> 01:20:29,838
I'm not sure. She said she'd had the croup before.
This could be pneumonia.

1265
01:20:32,508 --> 01:20:34,942
I keep telling her that,
and she doesn't want to.

1266
01:20:35,078 --> 01:20:36,443
You have to insist.

1267
01:20:36,512 --> 01:20:37,979
You shouldn't have done that.

1268
01:20:38,047 --> 01:20:39,412
- Please, let me out!
- Get in there!

1269
01:20:39,482 --> 01:20:40,813
Wanted to.

1270
01:20:41,417 --> 01:20:42,748
Felt good.

1271
01:20:42,919 --> 01:20:44,511
- Let me out! No! Please! No!
- You got her?

1272
01:20:46,055 --> 01:20:50,424
I lost two babies to back alley doctors.

1273
01:20:51,494 --> 01:20:52,825
No choice.

1274
01:20:56,199 --> 01:20:58,997
Never had the chance to fight for them.

1275
01:21:00,303 --> 01:21:01,600
You do.

1276
01:21:02,138 --> 01:21:03,503
Don't stop.

1277
01:21:05,108 --> 01:21:06,336
I won't.

1278
01:21:11,381 --> 01:21:14,680
Fuck them and the horse they rode in on.

1279
01:21:17,654 --> 01:21:19,918
That's not exactly language for a lady.

1280
01:21:20,957 --> 01:21:22,049
Hell.

1281
01:21:23,026 --> 01:21:26,826
There are times that's exactly
the right language to use.

1282
01:21:28,231 --> 01:21:29,323
Yeah?

1283
01:21:30,900 --> 01:21:33,425
When you've got nothing left to lose.

1284
01:21:34,103 --> 01:21:36,333
You're not supposed to be here!

1285
01:21:36,439 --> 01:21:38,100
Mmm. Mmm.

1286
01:22:00,463 --> 01:22:04,024
Stay there. Check the house.
Check the barn.

1287
01:22:13,710 --> 01:22:15,473
It's all clear.

1288
01:22:15,578 --> 01:22:17,409
Clear here.

1289
01:22:17,480 --> 01:22:19,414
Bring me that shovel.

1290
01:22:23,152 --> 01:22:25,484
All right. Let's go.

1291
01:22:30,793 --> 01:22:32,021
Come on.

1292
01:22:35,198 --> 01:22:37,393
You're gonna show me.

1293
01:22:43,206 --> 01:22:44,901
Come on. Show me.

1294
01:23:06,028 --> 01:23:07,256
This it?

1295
01:23:08,798 --> 01:23:10,095
You sure?

1296
01:23:10,166 --> 01:23:11,258
Yeah.

1297
01:23:14,203 --> 01:23:15,261
Dig.

1298
01:23:18,107 --> 01:23:22,043
You put them in the ground,
you can take them out of the ground.

1299
01:23:22,979 --> 01:23:24,776
Go on. Dig.

1300
01:23:25,681 --> 01:23:27,842
You heard me. Dig.

1301
01:24:13,095 --> 01:24:14,426
My God.

1302
01:24:16,632 --> 01:24:18,099
Oh, my God.

1303
01:24:31,647 --> 01:24:33,012
Call it in.

1304
01:24:33,549 --> 01:24:34,641
Get the coroner and every officer

1305
01:24:34,717 --> 01:24:36,912
in a 20-mile radius here inside the hour.

1306
01:24:36,986 --> 01:24:40,285
Then put out an APB
on Gordon Stewart Northcott.

1307
01:24:41,424 --> 01:24:43,949
The information's in my car.
Go on.

1308
01:24:49,532 --> 01:24:51,193
You can stop, son.

1309
01:24:56,172 --> 01:24:58,037
You can stop now.
It's over.

1310
01:24:58,107 --> 01:24:59,369
Hey.

1311
01:24:59,442 --> 01:25:03,674
We'll take it, we can take it from here.
We can take it from...

1312
01:25:09,018 --> 01:25:12,476
We can take it from here, okay?
It's over.

1313
01:25:18,194 --> 01:25:19,855
It's okay.

1314
01:25:22,465 --> 01:25:24,160
It's okay. It's okay.

1315
01:25:24,767 --> 01:25:26,064
It's all over.

1316
01:25:26,502 --> 01:25:27,594
Okay?

1317
01:25:29,705 --> 01:25:30,831
File.

1318
01:25:36,245 --> 01:25:37,769
Privacy, please.

1319
01:25:43,519 --> 01:25:46,977
I see that you've been refusing medication,
requiring force feeding.

1320
01:25:47,323 --> 01:25:49,291
All right, Michael.
Lunchtime?

1321
01:25:49,358 --> 01:25:52,452
Six days, Mrs. Collins,
and no progress.

1322
01:25:53,262 --> 01:25:56,789
We may have to move on
to more strenuous therapies.

1323
01:25:57,900 --> 01:26:01,529
Unless you're willing to prove
that you're doing better

1324
01:26:02,972 --> 01:26:04,701
by signing this.

1325
01:26:07,777 --> 01:26:10,610
Fuck you and the horse you rode in on.

1326
01:26:15,017 --> 01:26:16,541
Room 18.

1327
01:26:24,894 --> 01:26:28,022
I want to talk to somebody in charge,
right now!

1328
01:26:28,097 --> 01:26:29,359
Please.

1329
01:26:29,432 --> 01:26:31,457
Who is in charge here?

1330
01:26:33,669 --> 01:26:34,829
Open.

1331
01:26:35,404 --> 01:26:36,701
I'm the head doctor on duty.

1332
01:26:36,772 --> 01:26:39,036
You're the doctor who locked up
Christine Collins?

1333
01:26:39,108 --> 01:26:40,234
Oh, I'm sorry, sir.

1334
01:26:40,309 --> 01:26:41,833
We don't discuss cases
with anyone other than family.

1335
01:26:41,911 --> 01:26:44,505
Oh, you'll damn well discuss this one.
Read it.

1336
01:26:44,580 --> 01:26:45,604
Sir.

1337
01:26:45,681 --> 01:26:46,909
Read it.

1338
01:26:52,755 --> 01:26:53,813
Stop.

1339
01:27:02,331 --> 01:27:03,696
Mrs. Collins, one last time.

1340
01:27:03,766 --> 01:27:07,293
Are you or are you not
prepared to sign that letter?

1341
01:27:07,370 --> 01:27:08,598
No.

1342
01:27:12,808 --> 01:27:14,366
You're free to leave.

1343
01:27:17,780 --> 01:27:18,872
What?

1344
01:27:19,248 --> 01:27:22,740
Your clothes are in the next room.
You can change there.

1345
01:27:23,486 --> 01:27:24,510
In the next room?

1346
01:27:24,587 --> 01:27:26,214
Yes. That's right.

1347
01:27:27,256 --> 01:27:28,553
See to it.

1348
01:27:33,596 --> 01:27:34,756
Christ.

1349
01:27:35,264 --> 01:27:36,288
Long as it's not the original.

1350
01:27:36,365 --> 01:27:37,423
No, it's not.

1351
01:27:37,500 --> 01:27:38,899
Here it is.

1352
01:27:38,968 --> 01:27:40,799
And who is that?
Is that Baker's file or Larson?

1353
01:27:40,870 --> 01:27:42,098
That's Baker.

1354
01:27:42,171 --> 01:27:44,036
He said he wanted...

1355
01:27:44,106 --> 01:27:45,505
Nurse, I wanna see

1356
01:27:45,574 --> 01:27:48,702
every piece of paper you have
on the case of Mrs. Christine Collins,

1357
01:27:48,778 --> 01:27:50,769
and I want to see it right now,
do you understand me?

1358
01:27:50,846 --> 01:27:53,474
Every piece.
When will she be coming out?

1359
01:27:54,517 --> 01:27:55,541
Oh, it's just up ahead.

1360
01:27:55,618 --> 01:27:56,915
Oh, all right.
Let's...

1361
01:27:56,986 --> 01:27:59,216
Hurricane hits West Palm Beach!

1362
01:27:59,288 --> 01:28:01,756
Babe Ruth hits 53rd home run!

1363
01:28:02,725 --> 01:28:04,716
- Kids found murdered in Riverside!
- There it is.

1364
01:28:04,794 --> 01:28:07,661
Biggest crime in Los Angeles history!

1365
01:28:07,730 --> 01:28:09,789
Collins boy assumed dead!

1366
01:28:11,000 --> 01:28:13,491
Read it here!
Read it here!

1367
01:28:18,808 --> 01:28:20,901
Mrs. Collins, I'm so sorry.

1368
01:28:25,347 --> 01:28:27,611
Captain, your handling
of the Christine Collins case

1369
01:28:27,683 --> 01:28:30,743
has exposed this department to public ridicule.

1370
01:28:31,353 --> 01:28:35,153
There is even the possibility
of civil and criminal liability.

1371
01:28:35,624 --> 01:28:38,491
Sir, nobody could've known
what was happening up at that ranch.

1372
01:28:38,561 --> 01:28:41,621
Not us, the sheriff's department,
or the marshal's office.

1373
01:28:41,697 --> 01:28:43,790
And as for the Collins woman,

1374
01:28:43,866 --> 01:28:46,630
I'm still not convinced that her boy
is among the victims up in Wineville.

1375
01:28:46,769 --> 01:28:47,861
No?

1376
01:28:47,937 --> 01:28:48,904
No.

1377
01:28:48,971 --> 01:28:52,463
There were four other photos of missing boys
that looked a lot like him.

1378
01:28:52,541 --> 01:28:54,475
The Clark kid could've been mistaken.

1379
01:28:54,543 --> 01:28:55,874
Maybe he was.

1380
01:28:55,945 --> 01:28:59,176
Which begs the obvious question.
Who cares?

1381
01:29:00,583 --> 01:29:01,675
Sir?

1382
01:29:01,917 --> 01:29:04,112
The mayor wants this to go away.

1383
01:29:04,186 --> 01:29:06,279
I want this to go away.

1384
01:29:06,355 --> 01:29:09,847
The way you do that
is to stop insisting that Walter Collins

1385
01:29:09,925 --> 01:29:12,450
is not among those boys
killed up at that goddamn ranch.

1386
01:29:12,528 --> 01:29:15,088
Because if the boy you brought back
is not Walter Collins,

1387
01:29:15,164 --> 01:29:18,156
and he's not dead up at that ranch,
then where the hell is he?

1388
01:29:18,234 --> 01:29:19,929
People are gonna want to know
why we haven't found him.

1389
01:29:20,002 --> 01:29:22,266
Why we're not doing our job.

1390
01:29:22,972 --> 01:29:25,065
But if, on the other hand,

1391
01:29:25,141 --> 01:29:29,407
he is, or could be,
among those poor boys killed up in Wineville,

1392
01:29:29,879 --> 01:29:32,211
then the inquiries stop.

1393
01:29:33,949 --> 01:29:35,507
It's a momentary embarrassment

1394
01:29:35,584 --> 01:29:37,711
you're just gonna have to live with.

1395
01:29:37,786 --> 01:29:39,253
Better a short inconvenience

1396
01:29:39,321 --> 01:29:42,484
than a lingering problem,
wouldn't you say, Captain?

1397
01:29:42,558 --> 01:29:43,718
Yes, sir.

1398
01:29:43,792 --> 01:29:45,657
The boy's been gone nearly a year.

1399
01:29:45,728 --> 01:29:48,891
If he was going to be found,
it would've happened by now.

1400
01:29:48,964 --> 01:29:50,329
Whether he was up at that ranch or not,

1401
01:29:50,399 --> 01:29:52,594
the truth is he probably is dead somewhere.

1402
01:29:52,668 --> 01:29:56,729
Better his mother accept that now than later,
don't you think?

1403
01:29:56,805 --> 01:29:58,796
- Yes, sir.
- Good.

1404
01:29:58,874 --> 01:30:00,501
That'll be all, Captain.

1405
01:30:02,211 --> 01:30:05,874
That's how you want it,
then I guess we're done here.

1406
01:30:06,081 --> 01:30:07,742
Tell county jail we're remanding him for trial.

1407
01:30:07,816 --> 01:30:11,684
Wait. I didn't do anything.
I wasn't even here when it happened.

1408
01:30:12,888 --> 01:30:14,219
By pretending to be Walter Collins,

1409
01:30:14,290 --> 01:30:17,782
you're interfering in a police investigation
of a kidnapping and murder.

1410
01:30:17,860 --> 01:30:20,852
We can try you as accomplice to that murder
after the fact.

1411
01:30:20,930 --> 01:30:22,363
That's too bad.

1412
01:30:22,431 --> 01:30:26,162
County jail is a lot worse
than a juvenile hall or a foster home.

1413
01:30:26,235 --> 01:30:27,634
It's a lot worse.

1414
01:30:29,638 --> 01:30:32,129
You can't do that.
I'm just a kid.

1415
01:30:34,643 --> 01:30:36,668
Sanford Clark's a kid, too.

1416
01:30:36,745 --> 01:30:39,213
Fifteen.
He's going to jail.

1417
01:30:39,281 --> 01:30:43,479
All murderers and their accomplices go to jail.
Everybody knows that.

1418
01:30:45,654 --> 01:30:48,384
Get him out of here.
It's out of my hands now.

1419
01:30:48,457 --> 01:30:50,982
Wait. I don't want to go to jail.

1420
01:31:01,237 --> 01:31:02,499
Prove it.

1421
01:31:04,173 --> 01:31:05,470
I...

1422
01:31:05,608 --> 01:31:09,135
I knew Los Angeles is
where they make the Tom Mix movies.

1423
01:31:09,812 --> 01:31:11,712
I figured if I could meet Tom Mix

1424
01:31:11,780 --> 01:31:14,476
maybe he would let me ride on his horse.

1425
01:31:16,018 --> 01:31:18,578
His horse is named Tony.
Did you know that?

1426
01:31:22,891 --> 01:31:24,290
How are you feeling?

1427
01:31:24,360 --> 01:31:25,725
All right.

1428
01:31:26,462 --> 01:31:28,191
The police still have a car outside.

1429
01:31:28,264 --> 01:31:32,132
I guess they're waiting to see
what your next move is going to be.

1430
01:31:33,269 --> 01:31:35,294
- I'm going home.
- And then?

1431
01:31:35,771 --> 01:31:37,705
Then, I've been giving it
a lot of thought.

1432
01:31:37,773 --> 01:31:42,267
And what they did to those women,
and what they did about Walter.

1433
01:31:43,145 --> 01:31:46,808
I used to always tell him,
"You never start a fight, but you always finish it."

1434
01:31:46,882 --> 01:31:50,283
And I didn't start this fight,
but I'm gonna finish it.

1435
01:31:50,886 --> 01:31:54,084
Mrs. Collins, right now
you're a sufficiently high profile

1436
01:31:55,157 --> 01:31:58,991
that I think even the police would hesitate
to go after you out in the open,

1437
01:31:59,461 --> 01:32:01,861
but I have to warn you
that could change very quickly

1438
01:32:01,930 --> 01:32:04,626
if they feel their position threatened.

1439
01:32:04,700 --> 01:32:06,497
Very quickly indeed.

1440
01:32:07,870 --> 01:32:10,202
What are they gonna do to me now?

1441
01:32:12,107 --> 01:32:13,734
They got nothing.

1442
01:32:16,745 --> 01:32:18,269
I'm going home.

1443
01:32:42,004 --> 01:32:43,403
Hi, sis.

1444
01:32:44,139 --> 01:32:45,470
Gordon.

1445
01:32:45,541 --> 01:32:48,032
I didn't know you were back in town.

1446
01:32:48,711 --> 01:32:50,872
Yeah, I got in a couple of days ago,

1447
01:32:50,946 --> 01:32:53,813
figured I'd surprise you.
Is that... Is that okay?

1448
01:32:53,882 --> 01:32:56,908
Yes. Yes, of course.
Of course, come on in.

1449
01:32:59,822 --> 01:33:02,120
Where's that little niece of mine?

1450
01:33:02,191 --> 01:33:04,318
She went into town.

1451
01:33:04,393 --> 01:33:05,883
Should be back this evening.

1452
01:33:05,961 --> 01:33:07,155
Uh, Bob's here.

1453
01:33:07,229 --> 01:33:08,287
Oh, good.

1454
01:33:08,364 --> 01:33:10,696
Uh, I was gonna ask
if I could stay on a couple days.

1455
01:33:10,766 --> 01:33:12,131
Staying?

1456
01:33:12,534 --> 01:33:13,660
Yeah.

1457
01:33:13,736 --> 01:33:16,000
Listen, can I use your bathroom?

1458
01:33:16,071 --> 01:33:18,062
It's been a long ride
and I could really use a shower.

1459
01:33:18,140 --> 01:33:20,074
- Of course.
- Okay.

1460
01:33:20,843 --> 01:33:22,208
Thank you.

1461
01:33:36,592 --> 01:33:37,820
Is that...

1462
01:33:38,026 --> 01:33:41,393
All right, go next door.
I'll call the police. Hurry.

1463
01:33:46,168 --> 01:33:47,863
<i>Operator.
How may I connect you?</i>

1464
01:33:48,437 --> 01:33:49,495
He's upstairs, sir.

1465
01:33:49,571 --> 01:33:52,335
Go around the other side!
Cut him off!

1466
01:33:52,408 --> 01:33:53,466
- Come with me!
- Yes, sir.

1467
01:33:53,542 --> 01:33:54,839
Let's go!

1468
01:33:59,014 --> 01:34:02,882
Mrs. Collins, I'd like you
to meet my friend, Mr. Hahn.

1469
01:34:02,951 --> 01:34:06,580
Mrs. Collins, my deepest condolences on your loss.

1470
01:34:07,256 --> 01:34:08,814
May we come in?

1471
01:34:12,928 --> 01:34:14,828
I appreciate the sentiment,

1472
01:34:14,897 --> 01:34:17,127
but they've yet to find...

1473
01:34:17,199 --> 01:34:19,724
To identify the remains as my son.

1474
01:34:21,904 --> 01:34:24,395
I'm afraid it never gets any easier.

1475
01:34:24,973 --> 01:34:27,134
I lost a daughter to polio five years ago.

1476
01:34:27,209 --> 01:34:29,404
There's not a day goes by
when I don't think,

1477
01:34:29,478 --> 01:34:32,003
"I should mention this to Claudine."

1478
01:34:32,080 --> 01:34:34,446
Then I remember she's not here.

1479
01:34:37,319 --> 01:34:38,616
Please, sit.

1480
01:34:43,559 --> 01:34:45,493
I've been on the phone all morning

1481
01:34:45,561 --> 01:34:48,758
with the appointment secretary
of the police commission.

1482
01:34:48,831 --> 01:34:50,799
They said that they won't let me testify

1483
01:34:50,866 --> 01:34:54,131
at the hearing or call witnesses.
That it won't be necessary.

1484
01:34:54,203 --> 01:34:56,797
I know.
My sources say the police commission

1485
01:34:56,872 --> 01:35:00,968
is going to say that Jones and the LAPD
did absolutely nothing wrong,

1486
01:35:01,076 --> 01:35:04,136
and that the real blame lies
with the kid and with you

1487
01:35:04,213 --> 01:35:09,150
for being difficult and forcing them
to put you away for your own safety.

1488
01:35:12,488 --> 01:35:16,652
Then I guess I would have to hire a lawyer,
file a civil suit.

1489
01:35:17,459 --> 01:35:19,393
I went to the best attorney in town,

1490
01:35:19,461 --> 01:35:22,294
a man who's sued this city four times and won.

1491
01:35:22,364 --> 01:35:25,333
Unfortunately, we can't afford to really hire him.

1492
01:35:25,400 --> 01:35:26,628
I see.

1493
01:35:26,702 --> 01:35:29,193
Which is why I'm doing this pro bono.

1494
01:35:29,738 --> 01:35:33,071
It would be my honor to defend
your honor, Mrs. Collins.

1495
01:35:33,275 --> 01:35:34,640
In my 15 years as a lawyer,

1496
01:35:34,710 --> 01:35:38,510
I have never seen anyone fight
as long or as hard as you have,

1497
01:35:38,747 --> 01:35:41,910
in what is so clearly
in the cause of justice.

1498
01:35:42,684 --> 01:35:44,049
Thank you.

1499
01:35:44,620 --> 01:35:45,985
Let me see what's on the shelf.

1500
01:35:46,054 --> 01:35:47,385
I'll look.

1501
01:35:49,458 --> 01:35:50,550
Yes? May I...

1502
01:35:50,626 --> 01:35:51,957
My name is S.S. Hahn,

1503
01:35:52,027 --> 01:35:54,860
and I have a court order for the immediate release
of all women being detained

1504
01:35:54,930 --> 01:35:57,865
in this institution
under the designation code 12

1505
01:35:57,933 --> 01:36:01,164
pending a formal inquiry
into the reasons for their detainment.

1506
01:36:01,236 --> 01:36:03,397
I'm sorry, the doctor in charge is not here

1507
01:36:03,472 --> 01:36:04,996
- until the morning.
- Madam, let me be clearer.

1508
01:36:05,073 --> 01:36:07,837
Either you will produce the people named
in that court order,

1509
01:36:07,910 --> 01:36:11,471
or you will find yourself behind bars,
and I mean without a key.

1510
01:36:11,547 --> 01:36:14,675
- I can't authorize you...
- Madam, stand aside.

1511
01:36:24,660 --> 01:36:25,718
Can I see her now?

1512
01:36:25,794 --> 01:36:27,819
- Sure. Absolutely.
- How does she look?

1513
01:36:53,455 --> 01:36:55,423
All right, fellas, step back.
Let's give him room.

1514
01:36:55,490 --> 01:36:56,514
Here he is.

1515
01:36:56,592 --> 01:36:58,583
Mr. Northcott, any comment on your arrest?

1516
01:36:58,660 --> 01:36:59,820
Mr. Northcott, how are you feeling?

1517
01:36:59,895 --> 01:37:01,556
Oh, I'm feeling fine.

1518
01:37:01,630 --> 01:37:04,155
I've been on a little vacation,
as some of you know.

1519
01:37:04,232 --> 01:37:06,928
It was a really pleasant vacation.

1520
01:37:07,002 --> 01:37:10,233
The police have certainly provided me
with a lot of amusement.

1521
01:37:10,305 --> 01:37:11,738
How long you been in hiding?

1522
01:37:11,807 --> 01:37:13,069
How did you avoid capture?

1523
01:37:13,141 --> 01:37:14,403
Easy, easy.
That's far enough.

1524
01:37:14,476 --> 01:37:16,171
Well, I didn't, did I?

1525
01:37:16,244 --> 01:37:17,336
One more shot!

1526
01:37:17,412 --> 01:37:19,380
Have you seen your picture in the paper?

1527
01:37:19,448 --> 01:37:22,679
Didn't know anybody wanted me
until just recently.

1528
01:37:22,751 --> 01:37:24,343
Didn't even try.

1529
01:37:24,953 --> 01:37:28,013
My luggage still has my initials on it, fellas.

1530
01:37:28,090 --> 01:37:30,217
Did you know why the police were after you?

1531
01:37:30,292 --> 01:37:33,193
No, but I figured it'd be a good idea
if I were to just stay out of it.

1532
01:37:33,261 --> 01:37:34,285
Any remorse, sir?

1533
01:37:34,363 --> 01:37:39,062
Do you have anything to say
to the parents of the children you murdered?

1534
01:37:39,134 --> 01:37:40,829
No comment.

1535
01:37:40,902 --> 01:37:41,994
One more shot, this way!

1536
01:37:43,605 --> 01:37:46,267
Mayor Cryer.
This is unexpected.

1537
01:37:47,142 --> 01:37:48,666
So was this.

1538
01:37:48,744 --> 01:37:52,180
Subpoenas, requests for depositions, interrogatories.

1539
01:37:52,247 --> 01:37:55,842
All courtesy of Mr. Hahn and his new client,
Christine Collins.

1540
01:37:56,785 --> 01:37:58,343
You don't have to look them over
too closely, Chief.

1541
01:37:58,420 --> 01:38:01,184
Your own copies should be coming any time now.

1542
01:38:01,256 --> 01:38:03,690
The city council has also agreed
to look into this,

1543
01:38:03,759 --> 01:38:04,817
starting immediately.

1544
01:38:04,893 --> 01:38:05,951
God damn it!

1545
01:38:06,028 --> 01:38:08,758
I thought this was supposed to go away.

1546
01:38:09,398 --> 01:38:10,626
This is an election year.

1547
01:38:10,699 --> 01:38:12,189
I can't afford this kind of press.

1548
01:38:12,267 --> 01:38:15,498
It is going away, sir.
I've instructed Captain Jones to deal with it.

1549
01:38:15,570 --> 01:38:17,128
I'm afraid, falling on his sword

1550
01:38:17,205 --> 01:38:21,107
and saying he made a mistake
isn't going to be good enough, Chief.

1551
01:38:21,176 --> 01:38:24,634
If we take him out of the picture
for a while,

1552
01:38:24,713 --> 01:38:28,513
just might help calm things down
until the hearing's finished.

1553
01:38:46,168 --> 01:38:48,466
- What is happening?
- Didn't you hear?

1554
01:38:48,537 --> 01:38:50,300
It's the biggest protest I've ever seen.

1555
01:38:50,372 --> 01:38:51,634
- Protest?
- Yeah.

1556
01:38:51,707 --> 01:38:54,904
Over the Collins broad,
if you can believe that.

1557
01:39:04,486 --> 01:39:07,649
We want justice! We want justice!

1558
01:39:10,058 --> 01:39:11,650
Oh, my!

1559
01:39:18,133 --> 01:39:20,101
Mr. Harris.

1560
01:39:20,168 --> 01:39:23,467
The Lord works in mysterious ways, Mrs. Collins.

1561
01:39:24,706 --> 01:39:26,571
Boy, does he ever.

1562
01:39:43,859 --> 01:39:46,453
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
can I have your attention, please?</i>

1563
01:39:46,528 --> 01:39:51,090
There are more people gathered in this chamber
than have ever been in this room before.

1564
01:39:51,166 --> 01:39:54,863
Therefore, I ask you to refrain
from demonstrations of any kind.

1565
01:39:54,936 --> 01:39:56,426
Tell the truth! Tell the truth!

1566
01:39:56,505 --> 01:40:00,407
We are all here because we want to know
the real facts in this case.

1567
01:40:00,475 --> 01:40:04,605
And everybody is going to be heard
if we have to sit here for a week.

1568
01:40:04,679 --> 01:40:07,580
Mr. Thorpe, I don't see any members
of the police commission.

1569
01:40:11,086 --> 01:40:14,249
Are there any members
of the police department in the room?

1570
01:40:14,322 --> 01:40:16,187
Is Chief Davis here?

1571
01:40:17,592 --> 01:40:19,184
Is Captain Jones here?

1572
01:40:20,962 --> 01:40:22,361
Is there anybody here representing the police?

1573
01:40:22,430 --> 01:40:26,628
Mrs. Collins, could you come across the street
with me for just a moment?

1574
01:40:26,701 --> 01:40:28,896
There's something I think you should see.

1575
01:40:28,970 --> 01:40:30,995
Well, I hate to call a recess
before we've even started,

1576
01:40:31,072 --> 01:40:32,596
but I think a few phone calls are in order.

1577
01:40:36,845 --> 01:40:39,746
The police decided it'd be best
to keep this off the main docket

1578
01:40:39,848 --> 01:40:44,080
in order to avoid exactly the sort of chaos
we have across the street.

1579
01:40:56,731 --> 01:40:59,700
Mrs. Collins.
I'm Leanne Clay.

1580
01:41:00,502 --> 01:41:02,766
- This is my husband, John.
- Hi.

1581
01:41:03,672 --> 01:41:06,698
I just wanted to pass along my sympathies.

1582
01:41:06,975 --> 01:41:09,102
What we went through
waiting to hear anything

1583
01:41:09,177 --> 01:41:13,307
about our son David was bad enough,
now this.

1584
01:41:14,249 --> 01:41:18,208
But what the police did to you,
there was no call for that.

1585
01:41:18,286 --> 01:41:19,844
No call at all.

1586
01:41:22,858 --> 01:41:24,416
All rise.

1587
01:41:33,168 --> 01:41:35,193
- Please, be seated.
- Bailiff.

1588
01:41:48,450 --> 01:41:49,644
Oh, hey.

1589
01:41:51,853 --> 01:41:53,980
I saw you in the papers.

1590
01:41:54,055 --> 01:41:57,923
You got a lot of moxie,
standing up to the police like that.

1591
01:42:03,131 --> 01:42:05,065
The defendant will please rise.

1592
01:42:10,705 --> 01:42:12,798
Gordon Stewart Northcott,

1593
01:42:12,874 --> 01:42:17,038
you've been charged with three counts of murder
in the first degree,

1594
01:42:17,112 --> 01:42:21,811
with an additional 17 counts under review
by the district attorney's office.

1595
01:42:21,883 --> 01:42:23,510
How do you plea?

1596
01:42:24,920 --> 01:42:27,047
Oh, not guilty, Your Honor.

1597
01:42:30,825 --> 01:42:32,986
You may sit, Mr. Northcott.

1598
01:42:37,565 --> 01:42:42,502
In light of the defendant's penchant
for international travel, no bail will be set.

1599
01:42:42,570 --> 01:42:45,164
This court will hear preliminary motions
by tomorrow morning.

1600
01:42:45,240 --> 01:42:47,708
The boy, Walter Collins,

1601
01:42:47,776 --> 01:42:50,540
was reported as missing,
March 10, 1928.

1602
01:42:51,346 --> 01:42:53,974
We then instituted a nationwide search.

1603
01:42:54,049 --> 01:42:57,985
On August 18th, we received a cable
indicating that a boy

1604
01:42:58,053 --> 01:43:01,489
matching his description
was found in DeKalb, Illinois.

1605
01:43:01,556 --> 01:43:05,583
Upon questioning,
he admitted to being Walter Collins.

1606
01:43:05,660 --> 01:43:10,620
We then made arrangements for him
to be transported back to California.

1607
01:43:10,865 --> 01:43:13,333
Where Mrs. Collins told you
the boy was not her son.

1608
01:43:13,401 --> 01:43:15,164
Yes. She denied his identity

1609
01:43:15,236 --> 01:43:18,228
in spite of all of the evidence
pointing to the contrary.

1610
01:43:18,306 --> 01:43:21,400
But, as subsequent events have demonstrated,

1611
01:43:21,509 --> 01:43:23,170
she was correct.

1612
01:43:24,412 --> 01:43:26,277
So, what prompted you to send her

1613
01:43:26,348 --> 01:43:27,975
for psychological evaluation?

1614
01:43:28,049 --> 01:43:29,778
Whether or not this was in fact the correct boy

1615
01:43:29,851 --> 01:43:32,376
was not relevant to my decision.

1616
01:43:32,454 --> 01:43:34,615
Throughout this period,
she acted strangely.

1617
01:43:34,689 --> 01:43:38,216
She was often cool
and aloof and unemotional,

1618
01:43:38,293 --> 01:43:41,956
especially when confronted with the boy
we found in DeKalb

1619
01:43:42,030 --> 01:43:44,089
and in our subsequent conversation.

1620
01:43:44,165 --> 01:43:47,030
It was because of her disturbing behavior

1621
01:43:47,835 --> 01:43:51,534
that I submitted her for observation

1622
01:43:51,606 --> 01:43:54,404
to the psychopathic ward
of Los Angeles County General Hospital.

1623
01:43:54,476 --> 01:43:55,773
Just like that.

1624
01:43:55,844 --> 01:43:58,039
You snap your fingers and an innocent woman

1625
01:43:58,113 --> 01:43:59,808
is thrown into the psycho ward!

1626
01:43:59,881 --> 01:44:03,214
- She wasn't thrown.
- Every family in this state is in grave danger

1627
01:44:03,284 --> 01:44:06,412
when a police captain
can take a woman into his office

1628
01:44:06,521 --> 01:44:07,818
and five minutes later

1629
01:44:07,889 --> 01:44:10,619
have her thrown into the psychopathic
ward on his own authority!

1630
01:44:10,692 --> 01:44:12,091
She wasn't thrown.

1631
01:44:12,160 --> 01:44:15,493
She wasn't thrown!
She wasn't thrown!

1632
01:44:16,164 --> 01:44:18,064
What was that, Captain?

1633
01:44:18,666 --> 01:44:20,861
She wasn't thrown.
She was escorted.

1634
01:44:24,606 --> 01:44:28,133
Escorted, thrown,
the verb doesn't matter, Captain.

1635
01:44:28,209 --> 01:44:32,441
What does matter is that her incarceration
was ordered without a warrant.

1636
01:44:32,514 --> 01:44:34,448
I am holding a carbon copy

1637
01:44:34,516 --> 01:44:37,644
of the affidavit of insanity
that was issued in the case

1638
01:44:37,719 --> 01:44:41,155
of the State of California
v. Christine Collins.

1639
01:44:41,222 --> 01:44:42,689
Who signed the affidavit?

1640
01:44:42,757 --> 01:44:43,849
I did.

1641
01:44:43,925 --> 01:44:46,553
Well, now, let me see
if I have this correct,

1642
01:44:46,628 --> 01:44:50,223
a woman was thrown into the psychopathic ward
without a warrant,

1643
01:44:50,298 --> 01:44:52,459
because no warrant existed.

1644
01:44:52,534 --> 01:44:55,094
And when it was finally written
several days later,

1645
01:44:55,170 --> 01:44:57,536
there was no need to sign it
or to go to a judge

1646
01:44:57,605 --> 01:45:00,369
because she was already in the asylum!

1647
01:45:02,043 --> 01:45:03,135
Is this correct, Captain?

1648
01:45:03,211 --> 01:45:04,473
Technically, yes.

1649
01:45:04,546 --> 01:45:07,572
Extraordinary steps were necessary
because we were dealing...

1650
01:45:07,649 --> 01:45:09,480
We were dealing with an extraordinary situation.

1651
01:45:09,551 --> 01:45:12,247
Now, is it our fault that we were being deceived

1652
01:45:12,320 --> 01:45:15,118
by a boy who claimed to be Walter Collins?
No.

1653
01:45:15,890 --> 01:45:18,882
In light of his claims
and her disturbing behavior,

1654
01:45:18,960 --> 01:45:21,554
who wouldn't begin to think
that there was something the matter with her?

1655
01:45:21,629 --> 01:45:22,653
Because she questioned you?

1656
01:45:22,730 --> 01:45:24,925
No, because she wouldn't listen!

1657
01:45:24,999 --> 01:45:26,796
Because she insisted on being obstinate!

1658
01:45:26,868 --> 01:45:30,065
Because she tried to take matters
into her own hand,

1659
01:45:30,171 --> 01:45:31,934
best left to qualified officers!

1660
01:45:32,006 --> 01:45:33,701
Because once civil disobedience starts...

1661
01:45:33,775 --> 01:45:35,834
Because she was fighting
for the life of her son!

1662
01:45:35,910 --> 01:45:37,901
A boy who may have still been alive

1663
01:45:37,979 --> 01:45:42,643
while you were wasting valuable time
denying you had done anything wrong!

1664
01:45:45,386 --> 01:45:46,944
And in the end

1665
01:45:48,456 --> 01:45:51,186
that's what happened, isn't it?

1666
01:45:51,292 --> 01:45:54,750
At some point,
while all this was going on,

1667
01:45:56,931 --> 01:45:59,593
Walter Collins was brutally murdered,

1668
01:46:00,568 --> 01:46:02,968
along with as many as 19 other boys

1669
01:46:04,772 --> 01:46:07,434
at the Northcott Ranch in Wineville.

1670
01:46:09,244 --> 01:46:11,405
Is that correct, Captain?

1671
01:46:13,047 --> 01:46:14,537
Yes, it is.

1672
01:46:15,283 --> 01:46:16,910
It's a travesty.

1673
01:46:22,590 --> 01:46:24,421
No further questions.

1674
01:46:41,809 --> 01:46:43,800
<i>Train number 14,
now boarding on track...</i>

1675
01:46:43,878 --> 01:46:47,746
So, after much effort,
we were able to identify this boy,

1676
01:46:47,815 --> 01:46:50,375
who's been responsible
for so much trouble lately,

1677
01:46:50,451 --> 01:46:53,318
as Arthur Hutchins of Cedar Rapids, Iowa.

1678
01:46:54,122 --> 01:46:57,387
Between this, and the arrest of the man
suspected of murdering

1679
01:46:57,458 --> 01:46:59,187
the real Walter Collins,

1680
01:46:59,260 --> 01:47:02,525
we've cleared up two of the biggest mysteries
in the history of Los Angeles.

1681
01:47:02,597 --> 01:47:04,792
I hope you gentlemen of the press will give

1682
01:47:04,866 --> 01:47:06,925
as much space to the good things we do

1683
01:47:07,001 --> 01:47:09,561
as the mistakes that are made on rare occasions.

1684
01:47:09,637 --> 01:47:11,468
Gentlemen, allow me to introduce you

1685
01:47:11,539 --> 01:47:14,599
to the boy's real mother,
Mrs. Janet Hutchins.

1686
01:47:16,044 --> 01:47:17,511
Arthur.

1687
01:47:17,612 --> 01:47:19,102
I hope he wasn't too much trouble for you.

1688
01:47:19,180 --> 01:47:20,977
Oh, no, not at all.

1689
01:47:21,049 --> 01:47:23,244
How about a photograph, fellas?

1690
01:47:26,321 --> 01:47:27,720
One more.

1691
01:47:28,289 --> 01:47:29,722
Mrs. Hutchins,

1692
01:47:29,791 --> 01:47:33,124
Mrs. Collins, the woman he was staying with,
wanted him to have these.

1693
01:47:33,194 --> 01:47:34,684
They're the clothes she let him wear.

1694
01:47:34,762 --> 01:47:36,559
Well, thank you.

1695
01:47:36,631 --> 01:47:38,394
Isn't that nice, Arthur?

1696
01:47:38,466 --> 01:47:40,832
Tell the nice officer,
"Thank you."

1697
01:47:40,902 --> 01:47:43,894
I don't want them.
Give them to somebody else.

1698
01:47:43,972 --> 01:47:45,599
Precocious little fellow, isn't he?

1699
01:47:45,673 --> 01:47:47,971
It's not my fault.
It's the police.

1700
01:47:48,042 --> 01:47:51,671
They said I was Walter Collins, not me!
It wasn't my idea!

1701
01:47:51,746 --> 01:47:53,213
- Not my idea!
- Get...

1702
01:47:53,281 --> 01:47:55,715
Yeah. Go blame the police
for your own mistakes.

1703
01:47:55,783 --> 01:47:57,944
We've seen a lot of that lately,
haven't we?

1704
01:47:58,019 --> 01:48:00,954
Take care now, Arthur!
Safe travels.

1705
01:48:02,123 --> 01:48:04,353
All right, fellas, that's it for today.

1706
01:48:04,425 --> 01:48:06,154
Sir, sir!
What did the boy mean by that?

1707
01:48:06,427 --> 01:48:09,954
It was March 10th,
and I came home from work,

1708
01:48:10,031 --> 01:48:12,898
and my nine-year-old son, Walter,
was gone.

1709
01:48:12,967 --> 01:48:16,698
Captain Jones was acting on information
he believed to be correct.

1710
01:48:16,771 --> 01:48:20,400
Walter Collins had a diastema,
also known as a diastema.

1711
01:48:20,475 --> 01:48:21,999
That child was never in my classroom.

1712
01:48:22,110 --> 01:48:23,634
I can certainly attest to that.

1713
01:48:23,711 --> 01:48:27,078
We rely on our good friends
in the police department

1714
01:48:27,148 --> 01:48:30,208
to point to us those people who exhibit behavior

1715
01:48:30,285 --> 01:48:33,015
which is socially unacceptable.

1716
01:48:33,087 --> 01:48:37,922
About four inches shorter
than the last mark of Walter.

1717
01:48:38,793 --> 01:48:41,318
Well, some of these pictures show

1718
01:48:41,396 --> 01:48:44,058
what Sanford Clark told me,

1719
01:48:44,132 --> 01:48:47,727
that he did in fact help
in the murder of these children.

1720
01:48:47,802 --> 01:48:49,497
Thank you, Detective.

1721
01:48:49,570 --> 01:48:50,798
Gentlemen of the jury,

1722
01:48:50,872 --> 01:48:53,636
I ask you to take a good look at these images.

1723
01:48:53,708 --> 01:48:56,268
They establish beyond any reasonable doubt

1724
01:48:56,344 --> 01:49:00,110
the circumstances and the nature
of these heinous crimes.

1725
01:49:11,359 --> 01:49:13,224
I'm in here, Reverend.

1726
01:49:21,336 --> 01:49:23,463
When Walter was here,
I used to walk by his room

1727
01:49:23,538 --> 01:49:25,699
when he was sleeping.

1728
01:49:25,773 --> 01:49:29,766
And even though I couldn't see him
or hear him,

1729
01:49:29,844 --> 01:49:31,573
I could feel him.

1730
01:49:33,815 --> 01:49:36,545
That's why I don't think Walter's dead.

1731
01:49:37,885 --> 01:49:39,682
I can still feel him.

1732
01:49:42,323 --> 01:49:44,291
- Mrs. Collins...
- No.

1733
01:49:44,359 --> 01:49:46,554
I know what the police said.

1734
01:49:47,061 --> 01:49:49,621
But that place and the remains,

1735
01:49:51,499 --> 01:49:54,024
they couldn't be properly identified.

1736
01:49:55,036 --> 01:49:59,370
And maybe that kid made a mistake
when he picked Walter's picture.

1737
01:50:00,241 --> 01:50:03,642
I understand you don't want to accept this.

1738
01:50:03,711 --> 01:50:05,372
What mother would?

1739
01:50:08,683 --> 01:50:12,175
But I think it's time for you to move on

1740
01:50:12,286 --> 01:50:14,652
and start over for yourself.

1741
01:50:15,890 --> 01:50:18,324
Your son would want you to move on.

1742
01:50:20,495 --> 01:50:22,725
Maybe.

1743
01:50:22,797 --> 01:50:26,096
Maybe he'd want me to keep looking for him.

1744
01:50:26,167 --> 01:50:28,692
Maybe he's somewhere waiting for me.

1745
01:50:30,571 --> 01:50:32,801
I believe he is waiting, ma'am.

1746
01:50:34,308 --> 01:50:36,105
He's waiting in that place

1747
01:50:36,177 --> 01:50:40,204
where we'll all go someday
to be reunited with our loved ones.

1748
01:50:40,281 --> 01:50:45,378
And on that day, he'll know from front to back,
end to end,

1749
01:50:45,453 --> 01:50:48,980
heart to soul, that you did everything
you could, Mrs. Collins.

1750
01:50:50,358 --> 01:50:51,723
Everything.

1751
01:50:55,630 --> 01:50:57,325
We should go, ma'am.

1752
01:50:57,398 --> 01:50:58,763
One minute.

1753
01:51:25,660 --> 01:51:28,151
This meeting will now come to order.

1754
01:51:29,163 --> 01:51:32,189
This committee has now heard all of the testimony,

1755
01:51:32,266 --> 01:51:35,235
and, in light of the facts presented,

1756
01:51:35,336 --> 01:51:38,169
